What you need to know:  On Thursday, Spotika claimed that as soon as both parties signed the pre-contractual agreement on June 24 in Nairobi, AFC Leopards went behind their back and started negotiating another deal with a rival gaming companySpotika’s Marketing Manager, Alfred Otieno, absolved the company from blame, saying they learnt that AFC Leopards were negotiating with Betika, and were planning to pull out of the agreement soon after receiving the remaining Sh2 millionOn Thursday, AFC Leopards Secretary General Gilbert Andugu announced the termination of the agreement in a statement posted on the club’s social media platforms